castAddBody.text:
First day on Farcaster and wow.

This place honestly feels pretentious as heck. Not as messed up as Twitter or Bluesky but still leaves a lot to be desired.

Also...I think we need to talk about self-custody. After using a hardware wallet daily for years carrying a seedphrase in my laptop feels precarious as fuck.
Is it me or is the Yup mobile app the kind that'll make sure that everything gets posted or none of it does

The reason so many of you can never leave X dot com in the past is because you can't let go of the addiction you have to putting people down on that platform.

That's why y'all drag your shit to Farcaster, Bluesky, Lens and Threads - then complain that the "bad people" are ruining the platform.

Look in the fucking mirror. Farcaster is like watching people masturbate in public. The software stack isn't something I'm a fan of but neither am I a fan of the kind of content I see here. It's becoming like X in more ways than one.
While I appreciate the invitation to try this platform, this is exactly why I prefer hanging out on Lens. Lens ain't perfect but it's a far cry from the circlejerk that Farcaster is becoming.

That's another nail in Metamask's coffin...

Find a wallet that lets you care about your digital sovereignty instead of shoving an Infura RPC down your throat.

Let's add to that a loud reminder that Metamask is not the only Ethereum wallet in the App Store, neither is it the best.

Just because it's popular doesn't mean it's the best. Your family still uses WhatsApp despite you knowing it's one of the shittier messaging apps out there.

Warpcast Devs be delusional enough to call their PWA a "Desktop App" to the point that Farcaster blasted out an email about it.

Slow news day over there?

"Please ask a human artist to draw this"

I thought artists don't work for free?

I love how many kids go on Bluesky to shit on web3 while not realising that Bluesky is in itself a great example of an app that utilises web3 in its data routing.

It's web3 at its finest.
Ok rants over gn

To the nincompoop engagement farming bot on Lens that randomly roulettes a profile to like my posts without following me...


...i can't wait to block your asses on-chain.
It's not even 7.30 and the outside of the office looks like it's as dark as the night already...
Peel me off this velcro seat...

I swear everytime I open Farcaster it's always pretentious cryptobros trying to sound smartass.

Lens is literally NFT-powered and you see much less of that over there.

"the sign says self-service"

Bruh if I had to self-service my own dosa I'll make it at home.
Time to try to brain Lensv2. So much more to the protocol than I initially thought - and I knew it would be a big change.

One of my best friends is flying to the other side of the world to share his experiences & adventures - all on his own dime and precious off days from work.

Bunch of kids are already trying to fuck it up for him before he even boarded his flight.

Can't have a day without drama in this fandom.

I didn't wanna waste that last bird's-eye Chili in the varuval at dinner.

I was not equipped to prevent it from going to waste.
The waiting time at the caf√© I'm at is half as long as a lunch break...
And the Etherneum Mainnet is shitting itself again...
Rest in Peace, Binance. It was a good run.

How many commemorative NFTs is Farcaster going to make on Zora that claim to be "free" but chip away 0.000777 ETH plus gas fees for every mint.

There's so many other NFT minting platforms you can deploy on your own. We don't need this grift of a "mint fee".

Has Zora's VC money dried up?
Being a proofreader and copywriter now makes me realise how much I don't like being proofread by someone else.

I ate my Edamame this morning.

I earned this.
I got my family to use Google Keep. Simple enough for the folks to understand and sync shopping lists and stuff with me
This episode of Bluey is called

Happy New Ye-

SINCE WHEN WERE POWDERS REGULATED IN HAND-CARRY LUGGAGE!?

Is this where I bid farewell to the one-handed Ctrl+Alt-Delete kungfu?

https://gizmodo.com.au/2024/01/microsoft-introduces-the-first-new-windows-keyboard-key-in-decades-but-its-only-for-ai/

When I make coffee on the espresso machine, I usually make two cups.

The first pull is the strong, full-bodied espresso that I drink to savour and enjoy

The second is the filthy overextracted bean water that would make James Hoffman cry, which I drink so that i can stay awake.
Fuck you, Elon. Where's my hexagon?!
Web3 companies are such snowflakes in the branding department...

Wake up and first thing I read about are people actually buying testnet tokens.

How low are we gonna go.

Overheard at work today:

"zkSync is similar to the Op(timism) Stack"

*facedesk*
o no
Oh for fuck's sake, Gaben...
It's a free service therefore I'm not allowed to complain, right?
LRT braking is whack this morning. I feel like I'm being thrown to the front of the train when we stop at every station.
That old Malay newspaper went from erectile dysfunction to premature ejaculation in a day.
Solana maximalists need to shut the fuck up about their VC chain when theyre hanging out in Ethereum groups.

Every time I take the city bus I'm reminded why I hate taking the bus.

But it's a free service so fuck me, right?

Never thought that we'd find Amelia Earhart's plane before we found MH370...
https://www.abc.net.au/news/2024-01-31/deep-sea-vision-team-claims-amelia-earhart-plane-found/103407718

It's 2024. We have truly borderless means of monetary transfer that's available around the clock and get we're stuck reinventing the fucking wheel with EMV and shitty banks.

I don't know whether to be impressed, disappointed or livid at this point.
I appreciate how a colleague bothers to tell me "Daniel, I know you don't like Arbitrum but..." before asking about it.
The way so many Residents' Associations want to "maintain the image" of their apartment complexes is to make it look like no one actually lives there.

Dear designers

How the heck do you tolerate them big ass Figma files
Me while trying to open a massive Figma file on a crappy 8GB MacBook Air
when you're busy with a pull request but your mates send you a pool request

I wish GitBook goes up in flames one of these days. Fucking overpriced SaaS with shit-tier service.

Self-host your docs. If you can pay for GitBook, you can pay for hosting. You'll pay less even.

New journey, new responsibilities, new adventures.

Can't wait to see you, ETH Seoul <3

Seeing someone I despise get their ass dragged through the mud and feeling bad for them shook me up this morning.

I never thought I would empathise with them ever again.

I'm probably wasting time and energy at this point.
Buddy, I love what you're presenting but don't butcher the Solidity icon like that please...
I can hear a sports car tearing up the streets of Gangnam...
it's hecking 3am Incheon can i please check into my flight already
The shoving of all the $DEGEN posts on Farcaster has proven that the purple network has once again lost the plot of decentralised social media.
"Free on Zora" is bullshit. Nothing is free on a platform that swindles you for fees. The only fee you should be paying is for gas.
I'm taking $onchain pill. Dafuq does this thing do.

Today I read about stablecoin drama.

Was surprised at first but then remembered most stablecoins peg against the original shitcoin.

#token2049dubai #dubaifloods
